{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_019opNgYLNQ3vEYJqC6VTgsR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HTTPS access is restored — the curl test now returns `hello` with exit code 0.\n\n## Diagnosis\n\nThe Ingress `demo-ingress` (host `demo.example.com`) terminated TLS using secret `expired-tls-secret`, which contained a certificate that was **expired**:\n\n- `notBefore=Jan 1 2020`, `notAfter=Jan 2 2020` (CN=demo.example.com) — a 1-day cert that expired over 6 years ago.\n\nThat caused the `SSL certificate problem` / verification failures (curl exit 60) for HTTPS clients.\n\n## Fix\n\nThe validation CA mounted in the curl-test pod (`/tmp/tls/ca.crt`, CN=`Test CA`) is what clients trust, so the served cert had to be signed by *that* CA. I:\n\n1. Identified the in-cluster validation CA from the pod and matched its public key to the CA private key on the host (`/tmp/test-ca.key` / `/tmp/test-ca.crt`).\n2. Generated a fresh RSA key + certificate for `demo.example.com` (SAN `DNS:demo.example.com`, valid 2026→2028) signed by that CA, and confirmed `openssl verify` passes against the pod's CA.\n3. Replaced the contents of secret `demo/expired-tls-secret` with the new cert/key (`kubectl create secret tls ... --dry-run=client | kubectl apply`), so the Ingress definition didn't need to change.\n4. nginx-ingress hot-reloaded the secret; the curl validation now succeeds.\n\nVerification:\n```\ncurl --cacert /tmp/tls/ca.crt --resolve demo.example.com:31430:172.18.0.5 \\\n     https://demo.example.com:31430/\n→ hello   (exit 0)\n```\n\nNote: `/tmp/ingress_env` ships `INGRESS_NODE_IP=` empty; the working node IP is `172.18.0.5` (the control-plane node). The TLS fix itself is complete and verified."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":310,"cache_read_input_tokens":46951,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":310},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0dcf649d-54a0-437f-b4ef-4e090dcf6f6e","uuid":"825632b7-f39f-48b8-b291-14bacc029ce2","request_id":"req_011CcAbv6WaHEozZjpxVHAXx"}
